  "title": "Survey Designer (Full Stack Developer / 1 year contract )",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong><br />The ideal candidate will be responsible for developing and maintaining both front-end and back-end applications, ensuring high performance, security, and a seamless user experience.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Develop and maintain high-quality front-end applications using <strong>React JS; utilise Redux</strong> Toolkit for efficient state management</p></li><li><p>Design and implement high-performing backend applications using <strong>Node JS, Python, </strong>Streamlit; ensure the security and performance of backend applications</p></li><li><p>Should have knowledge to integrate AWS Cloud services</p></li><li><p>Conduct thorough code reviews and provide constructive feedback</p></li><li><p>Follow best practices for coding, testing, and deployment</p></li><li><p>Work closely with design and product teams to ensure a seamless user experience</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Experience in both frontend and backend development</p></li><li><p>Experience with ReactJS, Python, Redux, Streamlit</p></li><li><p>Experience in creation/maintenance of APIs using Node.js</p></li><li><p>Good knowledge of backend technologies and AWS Cloud services</p></li><li><p>Strong attention to detail and commitment to producing high-quality work</p></li><li><p>Ability to conduct thorough and constructive pull request reviews<br /></p><p><br /><em><strong>“This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (“e2i”).</strong></em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and employers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a bridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job security through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services, and partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment, training, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the National Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and skills upgrading initiatives. By applying for this role, you consent to RMA Groups’s PDPA and e2i’s PDPA.”</em></p></li></ul>",
